-- PRESS DIGEST - Bulgaria - Dec 4
-- 
-- Thu Dec 04, 2014 03:14AM EST
-- None



SOFIA, Dec 4 (Reuters) - These are some of the main stories in Bulgarian newspapers on Thursday. Reuters has not verified these stories and does not vouch for their accuracy.

-- Prime Minister Boiko Borisov will hold talks with the heads of the European Commission, European Council and European Parliament as the top issue on the agenda will be Russia's decision to abandon the South Stream pipeline project (Trud, Presa, Sega). -- The Sofia City Court has ruled that central bank's Deputy Governor Tsvetan Gunev is to vacate the office. In June, Gunev was charged with abuse of office (Capital daily, Trud, Standart). -- The interior ministry approved measures to step up security at bank offices where deposit holders will have access to their savings at Corporate Commercial Bank (Corpbank) <6C9.BB> (Sega, Presa). SEGA - In 2014, Bulgaria ranks lowest in the group of EU and western European countries in the annual corruption perceptions index, the Transparency International said. The Black Sea state was 69th among 175 countries worldwide.